TY  - JOUR
AU  - Riley, John G.
T1  - Ex Post Information in Auctions
PY  - 1988
Y1  - 1988/07/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297392
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 55
IS  - 3
SP  - 409
EP  - 429
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - When buyers' private information about the value of an item for sale is correlated, the seller can increase expected revenue in a sealed bid auction by making the winner's payment a function of information available after the end of the auction. Specifically, revenue can be increased by making the payment a function of all the losing bids. In addition there are gains to making the payment contingent upon some signal of the object's value which becomes public at a later date. That is, there are gains to introducing positive royalty rates.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297392
ER  - 



